# /pm — Project Management

Route based on arguments:
- No args → show status (call `pm_status`)
- `status` → detailed status dashboard
- `create story "<title>" "<description>"` → create a new story
- `create task <story-id> "<title>" "<description>"` → create a task
- `get <id>` → show item details
- `search <query>` → search items
- `update <id> <field>=<value>` → update an item
- `archive <id>` → archive an item
- `fix malformed` → fix quarantined malformed files (see /pm-fix)
- `repair` → run hub repair via `pm_repair`
- `sync` → pull latest across all hub submodules

Use the ProjectMan MCP server tools to fulfill these requests. Present results in clean, readable format.

## ID Conventions

- User Stories: `US-PREFIX-N` (e.g. `US-CEO-1`)
- Tasks: `PREFIX-N-N` (e.g. `CEO-1-1`)
- Filenames match the ID: `US-CEO-1.md`

## Hub Mode

When working in hub mode, many tools accept an optional `project` parameter to target a specific subproject (e.g. `pm_status(project="CEO-Frontend")`). Without it, tools operate on the hub root or scan all subprojects.
